text.tspan: NFSv4 Proxy in User Space on massive cluster architecture
Incohency issue between the proxy servers
NFSv4 Proxy is the chosen solution
Use of proxy is a classical way of reducing load
NFSv4 has aggressive caching capabilities that make
it possible to implement proxy server with efficient cache
"home made" nfs server running in user space
- it has a very large caching feature (up to millions of records)
- we have full control on the source code
Things would be ok if all proxy servers access the main nfs server in a read-only way
- but they will create and delete files, symlinks and directories
- they will do NFSv4 stateful operations (in particular delegations that are very interesting
Incoherencies in-between the proxy servers' caches will occur quickly
- most of the incoherencies will be related to the metadata cache
Several things can be done to avoid this incoherency issue
- this would fit for file management, but this won't help for metadata management
- NFSv4.1 directory delegations will probably help
The situation where several proxy servers are in front of a single main NFS server is very similar to the
situation where several NFS servers are accessing the same cluster file system
- the work done at CITI about NFSv4 on cluster file system will be helpful
- but cluster file system is designed to be accessed in a massively concurrent way and has specific
features for this. The main NFSv4 server may not have such features.
All proxy servers that access the same NFSv4 server should be aware of each other
- when a modification operation is made by a proxy server, it should advertise it to the other
- this will not produce additional load to the main NFSv4 server, only inter proxy server communication
- a protocol is required to handle inter proxy server communication
First approach is to replay NFSv4 Compound requests that modify the file system objects
- other proxy servers will invalidate the related cache entries to keep coherency
- it will be more efficient if the other proxy servers update their caches without
- Proxy servers will talk using NFSv4 protocol
- NFSv4 is flexible and pretty adaptable
- a new operation (OP4_PROXY_UPDATE) is used to tag the
- regular NFSv4 client won't see this operation, only proxy server will
NFsv4 Proxy servers is a key feature for accessing NFS exported
namespace in a massive cluster of machines
- tests will start soon to validate the design choices
We hope to have a stable implementation in 2Q 2009 or 3Q 2009
The source will be available as part of the nfs-ganesha project
Use of NFS in the compute center
NFS is widely used since the birth of the compute center
- it's easy to deploy and manage
The CEA is the French Atomic Energy Commission (Commissariat l'nergie
atomique). It is a public body established in October 1945 by General de
Gaulle. The CEA mission statement has two main objectives : to become the
leading technological research organization in Europe and to ensure that the
nuclear deterrent remains effective in the future.
CEA plays a major role in sustaining the French nuclear deterrent capability
in the long term. Since nuclear testing was finally ended in 1996, the
operation and safety of weapons in the French deterrent force have been
guaranteed by means of computer simulation. This demands a high level
of computing power, which is offered by the Tera supercomputer facility
based at the CEA/DIF center in Bruyeres le Chatel, near Paris.
